event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Control_L', 'Escape'].
description: Upon pressing the key combination 'Control_L' + 'Escape', no visible changes occurred on the Windows XP desktop.
outcome: The Start menu opened, displaying program shortcuts and system options. The Start button transitioned to a visually depressed state.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Alt_L', 'c'].
description: Upon pressing the key combination 'Alt_L' + 'c', no visual changes occurred on the Windows XP desktop.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Control_L', 'Escape'].
description: Upon pressing the key combination 'Control_L' + 'Escape', no observable changes occurred on the Windows desktop or its elements.
outcome: The Start button became highlighted, and the Start Menu opened, displaying program shortcuts and system options.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['c'].
description: Upon pressing the 'c' key, no visual changes were observed in the customized Windows XP Start Menu.
outcome: The mouse cursor changed to an hourglass icon.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Right'].
description: Upon pressing the 'Right Arrow' key, no visual changes occurred in the Control Panel window.
outcome: The 'Date, Time, Language, and Regional Options' icon became highlighted.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Right'].
description: Upon pressing the 'Right Arrow' key, the focus within the Control Panel's main area shifted to highlight the 'Display' icon to the right.
outcome: The 'Date, Time, Language, and Regional Options' icon is no longer highlighted.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['p', 'o'].
description: Upon entering the key sequence "po", no visual changes occurred within the Windows XP Control Panel.
outcome: A tooltip with the text "Install or remove programs and Windows components." appeared, overlayed on top of the "Add or Remove Programs" icon.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Return'].
description: Upon pressing the 'Return' key, no visual changes occurred in the Control Panel interface.
outcome: A new window titled "Power Options Properties" opened in front of the Control Panel.

description: Upon clicking the mouse, the "Power Options Properties" dialog box came into focus. No other changes in the dialog box state were observed.
outcome: The "System hibernates" dropdown menu changed its selected option to "After 4 hours". The system tray clock also updated slightly, likely just reflecting the passage of time.

description: Upon clicking the mouse, the "Turn off hard disks" dropdown menu within the "Power Options Properties" dialog box came into focus.
outcome: The system clock in the bottom right corner updated to display the current time.

description: Upon clicking "OK", the "Power Options Properties" dialog box closed.
outcome: The "OK" button changed to its pressed/highlighted state.

description: Upon clicking the mouse, no visual changes occurred within the Control Panel interface.
outcome: A dialog box titled "Display Properties" opened, allowing customization of window appearances and text. The address bar now indicates "Display Properties" as the current location.

event: The mouse clicked on Desktop Screen Saver AppearanceSettings.
description: Upon clicking "Screen Saver" within the Display Properties dialog box, the "Screen Saver" tab became active.
outcome: The "Screen Saver" tab was already active.

description: Upon clicking the mouse, the user interacted with the screen saver dropdown menu within the "Screen Saver" tab of the Windows XP Display Properties dialog box.
outcome: The screen saver dropdown menu expanded to reveal a list of available options.

description: Upon clicking the mouse, the user selected "None" from the screen saver dropdown menu.
outcome: The Display Properties dialog box, including the "Screen Saver" tab and all its controls, disappeared.

description: Upon clicking the mouse, the Control Panel window closed.
outcome: The screen transitioned to a blue background displaying a minimal set of elements: a "Start" button and a "Control Panel" button in the bottom left corner, a "Recycle Bin" icon and a clock in the bottom right corner, and several system tray icons.
